        <h2 class="title"><a href="/glacier-national-park-montana-panoramas">Glacier National Park / Montana Panoramas</a></h2>    <span class="submitted">Submitted by <a href="/user/brad" title="View user profile." rel="nofollow">brad</a> on Mon, 2005-12-12 23:08.</span>
    <span class="taxonomy"><ul class="links inline"><li class="first last taxonomy_term_1"><a href="/archives/cat_photography.html" rel="tag" title="" class="taxonomy_term_1">Photography</a></li>
</ul></span>
    <div class="content"><p>In the summer we did a road trip in the northwest, up to Calgary, through Banff in the summer and then to Oregon Country Fair.  The photojournal is not yet ready, but I have prepared some of the panos.  First, here is the Montana section, which means the <a href=http://pic.templetons.com/brad/pano/montana.html>Going to the Sun road through Glacier National Park</a>.   Truly one of the world&#8217;s great roads, I&#8217;m afraid the panos don&#8217;t do it justice.</p>

<p><a href=http://pic.templetons.com/brad/pano/montana.html><img width=95% src=http://pic.templetons.com/brad/pano/thumb/stmary.jpg></a></p>
