        <h2 class="title"><a href="/node/311">Can I get a dishwasher with soft edges?</a></h2>    <span class="submitted">Submitted by <a href="/user/brad" title="View user profile." rel="nofollow">brad</a> on Sun, 2005-12-11 01:06.</span>
    <span class="taxonomy"><ul class="links inline"><li class="first last taxonomy_term_14"><a href="/archives/cat_random_ideas.html" rel="tag" title="" class="taxonomy_term_14">Random Ideas</a></li>
</ul></span>
    <div class="content"><p>I don't know how many times I've gotten a scrape or cut from hitting a dishwasher door, while it's down, with my leg.  It's very annoying how the sides are always sharp. They don't make the seal, that's on the front, so there's no reason these sides couldn't be soft, or even hard rubber that won't cut you.   Perhaps some dishwashers I haven't owned do this, but I have yet to get one!</p>
</div>
    <div class="links">&raquo; <ul class="links inline"><li class="first blog_usernames_blog"><a href="/blog/brad" title="Read brad&#039;s latest blog entries." class="blog_usernames_blog">brad&#039;s blog</a></li>
